cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "AAIF — Autonomous Agent Interchange Format (Schema Commons SC-006)"
message: "If you use AAIF, please cite it using these metadata."
type: dataset
abstract: >-
  AAIF is an open, vendor-neutral standard for declaring AI agents so that an
  agent defined on one runtime can be imported and executed on another. It
  standardises the declaration of an agent — identity, model preferences and
  provider routing, tool catalogue (function/MCP/HTTP/OpenAPI), memory
  backends, multi-agent orchestration topology, deterministic routing
  conditions, runtime policy, telemetry, evaluation, compliance, provenance,
  and portable live state — independent of any single LLM vendor or agent
  framework. It is published as JSON Schema 2020-12 plus a JSON-LD context,
  with community-maintained extension registries and a self-certification
  conformance program.
keywords:
  - artificial intelligence
  - LLM agents
  - multi-agent systems
  - interoperability
  - open standard
  - agent portability
  - Model Context Protocol
  - JSON Schema
